{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01316JfqHr7X5sGM4fApghgb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comprehensive Project Overview:\n\n🔍 Project Structure:\n- This is a Quarkus-based Pet Clinic application\n- Java 21 is used as the target Java version\n- Maven is the build system\n- Uses Quarkus Platform version 3.30.5\n- Deployed using multiple Dockerfile variants (JVM, native, fast-jar)\n\n🏗 Main Packages:\n1. org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model\n2. org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner\n3. org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system\n4. org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet\n5. org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit\n\n🗂 Key Configuration Details:\n- Uses different database configurations for dev, test, and production\n- Dev/Test: H2 in-memory database\n- Production: PostgreSQL\n- Hibernate ORM configured with profile-specific settings\n- Supports SQL logging\n- Compression and decompression enabled for HTTP\n\n🔧 Build & Deployment:\n- Maven with Quarkus Maven Plugin\n- Container image generation using Jib\n- Kubernetes deployment configuration included\n- Native image profile available\n\n🧪 Testing:\n- JUnit 5 for testing\n- Rest Assured for REST API testing\n- Separate test resources and configurations\n\n📦 External Dependencies:\n- Quarkus REST\n- Quarkus REST Jackson\n- Quarkus REST Qute\n- Hibernate ORM Panache\n- PostgreSQL JDBC\n- WebJars for Bootstrap and Font Awesome\n\nWould you like me to dive deeper into any specific aspect of the project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"8cc54cb4-69a5-4757-b451-b0bcfeab87a2"}
