{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EV4utkedi153uYBfdbscCf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.i18n.Localized;\n     4→import io.quarkus.qute.i18n.Message;\n     5→\n     6→@Localized(\"es\")\n     7→public interface SpanishAppMessages extends AppMessages {\n     8→    \n     9→    @Override\n    10→    @Message(\"Buscar Propietario\")\n    11→    String find_owner();\n    12→\n    13→    @Override\n    14→    @Message(\"Editar Propietario\")\n    15→    String edit_owner();\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    @Message(\"Apellido\")\n    19→    String last_name();\n    20→\n    21→    @Override\n    22→    @Message(\"Añadir Propietario\")\n    23→    String add_owner();\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    @Message(\"Buscar Propietarios\")\n    27→    String find_owners();\n    28→\n    29→    @Override\n    30→    @Message(\"Nombre\")\n    31→    String name();\n    32→\n    33→    @Override\n    34→    @Message(\"Error\")\n    35→    String error();\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    @Message(\"Veterinarios\")\n    39→    String veterinarians();\n    40→\n    41→    @Override\n    42→    @Message(\"ninguna\")\n    43→    String none();\n    44→\n    45→    @Override\n    46→    @Message(\"Inicio\")\n    47→    String home();\n    48→\n    49→    @Override\n    50→    @Message(\"Dirección\")\n    51→    String address();\n    52→\n    53→    @Override\n    54→    @Message(\"Teléfono\")\n    55→    String telephone();\n    56→\n    57→    @Override\n    58→    @Message(\"Mascotas\")\n    59→    String pets();\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    @Message(\"Especialidades\")\n    63→    String specialties();\n    64→\n    65→    @Override\n    66→    @Message(\"Bienvenidos\")\n    67→    String welcome();\n    68→\n    69→    @Override\n    70→    @Message(\"Ciudad\")\n    71→    String city();\n    72→\n    73→    @Message(\"Fecha Nacimiento\")\n    74→    String birthdate();\n    75→\n    76→    @Override\n    77→    @Message(\"Mascotas y Visitas\")\n    78→    String pets_and_visits();\n    79→\n    80→    @Override\n    81→    @Message(\"Tipo\")\n    82→    String type();\n    83→\n    84→    @Override\n    85→    @Message(\"Añadir Visita\")\n    86→    String add_visit();\n    87→\n    88→    @Override\n    89→    @Message(\"Añadir Mascota\")\n    90→    String add_pet();\n    91→\n    92→    @Override\n    93→    @Message(\"Editar Mascota\")\n    94→    String edit_pet();\n    95→\n    96→    @Override\n    97→    @Message(\"Fecha Visita\")\n    98→    String visit_date();\n    99→\n   100→    @Override\n   101→    @Message(\"Mascota\")\n   102→    String pet();\n   103→\n   104→    @Override\n   105→    @Message(\"Descripción\")\n   106→    String description();\n   107→\n   108→    @Override\n   109→    @Message(\"Algo ha ocurrido...\")\n   110→    String something_wrong();\n   111→\n   112→    @Override\n   113→    @Message(\"Propietario\")\n   114→    String owner();\n   115→\n   116→    @Override\n   117→    @Message(\"Fecha\")\n   118→    String date();\n   119→\n   120→    @Override\n   121→    @Message(\"Visitas Anteriores\")\n   122→    String previous_visits();\n   123→\n   124→}\n   125→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"069a2318-a841-485d-a0ba-0d802e06c883"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0123zKM4PrG5z2KMRyHHNbgH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic;\n     2→\n     3→import static io.restassured.RestAssured.when;\n     4→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.is;\n     5→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.notNullValue;\n     6→import static org.hamcrest.core.IsNull.nullValue;\n     7→import static org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.ErrorExceptionMapper.ERROR_HEADER;\n     8→import io.quarkus.test.common.http.TestHTTPEndpoint;\n     9→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n    10→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n    11→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.OwnersResource;\n    12→\n    13→@QuarkusTest\n    14→@TestHTTPEndpoint(OwnersResource.class)\n    15→public class OwnersResourceTest {\n    16→\n    17→    @Test\n    18→    void findPage() {\n    19→        when().get(\"find\").then()\n    20→                .statusCode(200)\n    21→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(nullValue()));\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    @Test\n    25→    void findAll() {\n    26→        when().get(\"?lastName=\").then()\n    27→                .statusCode(200)\n    28→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(nullValue()));\n    29→\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @Test\n    33→    void existingOwner() {\n    34→        when().get(\"1001\").then()\n    35→                .statusCode(200)\n    36→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(nullValue()));\n    37→\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @Test\n    41→    void invalidOwner() {\n    42→        when().get(\"1\").then()\n    43→                .statusCode(200)\n    44→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(notNullValue()));\n    45→\n    46→    }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"edee4f5b-7d18-4736-9dde-8e08ffb379f8"}
