{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TWXwA3HHUCQScfvfuzs2xt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!doctype html>\n     2→<html>\n     3→\n     4→<head>\n     5→\n     6→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\" />\n     7→  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n     8→  <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n     9→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n    10→\n    11→  <title>PetClinic :: a Quarkus Framework demonstration</title>\n    12→\n    13→  <!--[if lt IE 9]>\n    14→    <script src=\"https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js\"></script>\n    15→    <script src=\"https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js\"></script>\n    16→    <![endif]-->\n    17→  <link rel=\"shortcut icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"/images/favicon.ico\">\n    18→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/webjars/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\">\n    19→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/petclinic.css\" />\n    20→\n    21→</head>\n    22→\n    23→<body>\n    24→\n    25→  <nav class=\"navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark\" role=\"navigation\">\n    26→    <div class=\"container\">\n    27→      <div class=\"navbar-header\">\n    28→        <a class=\"navbar-brand\" href=\"/\"><span></span></a>\n    29→        <button class=\"navbar-toggler\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#main-navbar\">\n    30→          <span class=\"navbar-toggler-icon\"></span>\n    31→        </button>\n    32→      </div>\n    33→      <div class=\"collapse navbar-collapse\" id=\"main-navbar\" style>\n    34→\n    35→        <ul class=\"nav navbar-nav me-auto\">\n    36→\n    37→          <li class=\"active\">\n    38→            <a href=\"/\" title=\"home page\">\n    39→              <span class=\"fa fa-home\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    40→              <span>{msg:home}</span>\n    41→            </a>\n    42→          </li>\n    43→\n    44→          <li>\n    45→            <a href=\"/owners/find\" title=\"find owners\">\n    46→              <span class=\"fa fa-search\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    47→              <span>{msg:find_owners}</span>\n    48→            </a>\n    49→          </li>\n    50→\n    51→          <li>\n    52→            <a href=\"/vets.html\" title=\"veterinarians\">\n    53→              <span class=\"fa fa-th-list\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    54→              <span>{msg:veterinarians}</span>\n    55→            </a>\n    56→          </li>\n    57→\n    58→          <li>\n    59→            <a href=\"/oups\" title=\"trigger a RuntimeException to see how it is handled\">\n    60→              <span class=\"fa exclamation-triangle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    61→              <span>{msg:error}</span>\n    62→            </a>\n    63→          </li>\n    64→\n    65→        </ul>\n    66→      </div>\n    67→    </div>\n    68→  </nav>\n    69→  <div class=\"container-fluid\">\n    70→    <div class=\"container xd-container\">\n    71→\n    72→      {#insert body}No body!{/} \n    73→\n    74→    </div>\n    75→  </div>\n    76→\n    77→  <script src=\"/webjars/bootstrap/5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n    78→\n    79→</body>\n    80→\n    81→</html>\n    82→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"7ef6e0c3-106f-485b-8097-519906356f2a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011LcDKwpCkHFfGL4E9gbpna","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In Thymeleaf, layout/fragment inheritance works differently from Qute. Since we don't have Thymeleaf layout dialect in our dependencies, I'll use Thymeleaf's `th:replace` fragment approach or simply inline the base layout into each template. The simplest approach is to use Thymeleaf's fragment mechanism with `th:insert`/`th:replace`.\n\nActually, the simplest and most reliable approach is to NOT use Thymeleaf layout dialect (which would need extra dependencies) and instead create a utility method in TemplateEngine that wraps content in the base layout. Let me update the TemplateEngine and rewrite all templates:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1297,"cache_read_input_tokens":125282,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1297,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":278},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"f41e392c-47ed-44ab-8c74-742109b838cb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011LcDKwpCkHFfGL4E9gbpna","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01NwGNv5QpgBtu5fEKqQgK2J","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/system/TemplateEngine.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1297,"cache_read_input_tokens":125282,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1297,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":278},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"c549b249-8697-4659-8900-a397ce44de43"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NwGNv5QpgBtu5fEKqQgK2J","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→\n     6→import org.thymeleaf.context.Context;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.Locale;\n     9→import java.util.Map;\n    10→\n    11→/**\n    12→ * CDI-managed Thymeleaf template engine.\n    13→ * Replaces Quarkus Qute templating with standard Thymeleaf.\n    14→ */\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→public class TemplateEngine {\n    17→\n    18→    private org.thymeleaf.TemplateEngine engine;\n    19→\n    20→    @PostConstruct\n    21→    public void init() {\n    22→        engine = new org.thymeleaf.TemplateEngine();\n    23→        org.thymeleaf.templateresolver.ClassLoaderTemplateResolver resolver =\n    24→                new org.thymeleaf.templateresolver.ClassLoaderTemplateResolver();\n    25→        resolver.setPrefix(\"templates/\");\n    26→        resolver.setSuffix(\".html\");\n    27→        resolver.setTemplateMode(org.thymeleaf.templatemode.TemplateMode.HTML);\n    28→        resolver.setCharacterEncoding(\"UTF-8\");\n    29→        resolver.setCacheable(true);\n    30→        engine.setTemplateResolver(resolver);\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    public String render(String templateName, Map<String, Object> variables) {\n    34→        Context ctx = new Context(Locale.getDefault());\n    35→        // Add all message keys as variables\n    36→        Map<String, String> messages = AppMessages.getMessages();\n    37→        ctx.setVariable(\"msg\", messages);\n    38→        if (variables != null) {\n    39→            variables.forEach(ctx::setVariable);\n    40→        }\n    41→        return engine.process(templateName, ctx);\n    42→    }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"2804afb7-175e-4042-87fd-53202b8bb34c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01QtZN3WHYgNP4eUbkuu5s5f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me rewrite all the Thymeleaf templates. I'll remove the Qute `{#include base}` layout system and instead use Thymeleaf's fragment approach. The simplest pattern: each template will be a full page that includes the base layout via `th:replace`:\n\nLet me delete the existing templates and create new Thymeleaf ones:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":915,"cache_read_input_tokens":126579,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":915,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":168},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"54cf8e0f-f7ba-4f26-94a7-034edfb33928"}
