{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LNo1iKUdVLbb4BvZwo7QUz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     6→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     8→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    18→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.TemplateEngine;\n    19→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    20→\n    21→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    22→import java.util.Collection;\n    23→import java.util.Collections;\n    24→import java.util.HashMap;\n    25→import java.util.List;\n    26→import java.util.Map;\n    27→import java.util.Set;\n    28→\n    29→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    30→public class OwnersResource {\n    31→\n    32→    @Inject\n    33→    TemplateEngine templateEngine;\n    34→\n    35→    @Inject\n    36→    Validator validator;\n    37→\n    38→    @PersistenceContext\n    39→    EntityManager em;\n    40→\n    41→    @GET\n    42→    @Path(\"/find\")\n    43→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    44→    public String findTemplate() {\n    45→        Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n    46→        vars.put(\"errors\", Collections.emptyList());\n    47→        return templateEngine.render(\"findOwners\", vars);\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @GET\n    51→    @Path(\"new\")\n    52→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    53→    public String createTemplate() {\n    54→        Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n    55→        vars.put(\"owner\", null);\n    56→        vars.put(\"errors\", new HashMap<>());\n    57→        return templateEngine.render(\"createOrUpdateOwnerForm\", vars);\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    @GET\n    61→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/edit\")\n    62→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    63→    public String editTemplate(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) {\n    64→        Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    65→        Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n    66→        vars.put(\"owner\", owner);\n    67→        vars.put(\"errors\", new HashMap<>());\n    68→        return templateEngine.render(\"createOrUpdateOwnerForm\", vars);\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    @GET\n    72→    @Path(\"{ownerId}\")\n    73→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    74→    public String showOwner(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) {\n    75→        Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    76→        Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n    77→        vars.put(\"owner\", owner);\n    78→        return templateEngine.render(\"ownerDetails\", vars);\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    @POST\n    82→    @Path(\"new\")\n    83→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    84→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    85→    @Transactional\n    86→    public String processCreationForm(\n    87→            @FormParam(\"firstName\") String firstName,\n    88→            @FormParam(\"lastName\") String lastName,\n    89→            @FormParam(\"address\") String address,\n    90→            @FormParam(\"city\") String city,\n    91→            @FormParam(\"telephone\") String telephone) {\n    92→\n    93→        Owner owner = new Owner();\n    94→        owner.firstName = firstName;\n    95→        owner.lastName = lastName;\n    96→        owner.address = address;\n    97→        owner.city = city;\n    98→        owner.telephone = telephone;\n    99→\n   100→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   101→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   102→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   103→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   104→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   105→            }\n   106→            Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n   107→            vars.put(\"owner\", null);\n   108→            vars.put(\"errors\", errors);\n   109→            return templateEngine.render(\"createOrUpdateOwnerForm\", vars);\n   110→        } else {\n   111→            em.persist(owner);\n   112→            Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n   113→            vars.put(\"owner\", owner);\n   114→            return templateEngine.render(\"ownerDetails\", vars);\n   115→        }\n   116→    }\n   117→\n   118→    @POST\n   119→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/edit\")\n   120→    @Transactional\n   121→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   122→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   123→    public String processUpdateOwnerForm(\n   124→            @FormParam(\"firstName\") String firstName,\n   125→            @FormParam(\"lastName\") String lastName,\n   126→            @FormParam(\"address\") String address,\n   127→            @FormParam(\"city\") String city,\n   128→            @FormParam(\"telephone\") String telephone,\n   129→            @PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) {\n   130→\n   131→        Owner owner = new Owner();\n   132→        owner.id = ownerId;\n   133→        owner.firstName = firstName;\n   134→        owner.lastName = lastName;\n   135→        owner.address = address;\n   136→        owner.city = city;\n   137→        owner.telephone = telephone;\n   138→\n   139→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   140→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   141→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   142→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   143→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   144→            }\n   145→            Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n   146→            vars.put(\"owner\", owner);\n   147→            vars.put(\"errors\", errors);\n   148→            return templateEngine.render(\"createOrUpdateOwnerForm\", vars);\n   149→        } else {\n   150→            Owner merged = em.merge(owner);\n   151→            Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n   152→            vars.put(\"owner\", merged);\n   153→            return templateEngine.render(\"ownerDetails\", vars);\n   154→        }\n   155→    }\n   156→\n   157→    @GET\n   158→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   159→    public String processFindForm(@QueryParam(\"lastName\") String lastName) {\n   160→\n   161→        List<Owner> owners;\n   162→\n   163→        if (lastName == null || \"\".equals(lastName.trim())) {\n   164→            owners = em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o\", Owner.class).getResultList();\n   165→        } else {\n   166→            owners = em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o WHERE o.lastName = :lastName\", Owner.class)\n   167→                    .setParameter(\"lastName\", lastName)\n   168→                    .getResultList();\n   169→        }\n   170→\n   171→        if (owners.isEmpty()) {\n   172→            Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n   173→            List<String> errorList = new ArrayList<>();\n   174→            errorList.add(\"lastName not found\");\n   175→            vars.put(\"errors\", errorList);\n   176→            return templateEngine.render(\"findOwners\", vars);\n   177→        }\n   178→        if (owners.size() == 1) {\n   179→            Owner owner = owners.get(0);\n   180→            setVisits(owner);\n   181→            Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n   182→            vars.put(\"owner\", owner);\n   183→            return templateEngine.render(\"ownerDetails\", vars);\n   184→        }\n   185→\n   186→        Map<String, Object> vars = new HashMap<>();\n   187→        vars.put(\"owners\", owners);\n   188→        return templateEngine.render(\"ownersList\", vars);\n   189→    }\n   190→\n   191→    protected void setVisits(Owner owner) {\n   192→        if (owner.pets != null) {\n   193→            for (Pet pet : owner.pets) {\n   194→                List<Visit> visits = em.createQuery(\"SELECT v FROM Visit v WHERE v.petId = :petId\", Visit.class)\n   195→                        .setParameter(\"petId\", pet.id)\n   196→                        .getResultList();\n   197→                pet.setVisitsInternal(visits);\n   198→            }\n   199→        }\n   200→    }\n   201→\n   202→    @Path(\"/api/list\")\n   203→    @GET\n   204→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   205→    public List<Owner> listOwners() {\n   206→        return em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o\", Owner.class).getResultList();\n   207→    }\n   208→}\n   209→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"cf5b9a88-bbfd-4856-a34f-d4d765dc7200"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Qm76cV6yLWRP3XL4bPh9RS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.HashSet;\n     4→import java.util.Set;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    12→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Digits;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    14→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model.Person;\n    15→\n    16→@Entity\n    17→@Table(name = \"owners\")\n    18→public class Owner extends Person {\n    19→\n    20→    @Column(name = \"address\")\n    21→    @NotEmpty\n    22→    public String address;\n    23→\n    24→    @Column(name = \"city\")\n    25→    @NotEmpty\n    26→    public String city;\n    27→\n    28→    @Column(name = \"telephone\")\n    29→    @NotEmpty\n    30→    @Digits(fraction = 0, integer = 10)\n    31→    public String telephone;\n    32→\n    33→    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy = \"owner\", fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n    34→    public Set<Pet> pets;\n    35→\n    36→    public void addPet(Pet pet) {\n    37→        getPetsInternal().add(pet);\n    38→        pet.owner = this;\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    protected Set<Pet> getPetsInternal() {\n    42→        if (this.pets == null) {\n    43→            this.pets = new HashSet<>();\n    44→        }\n    45→        return this.pets;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @Override\n    49→    public String toString() {\n    50→        return \"Owner [address=\" + address + \", city=\" + city + \", pets=\" + pets + \", telephone=\" + telephone + \"]\";\n    51→    }\n    52→}\n    53→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"65f41ce4-f034-4d5f-931e-0c5e11cc2d4e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UnAs9GENZy1RxADCPUWhwd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.GenerationType;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.MappedSuperclass;\n     8→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     9→\n    10→@MappedSuperclass\n    11→public class Person {\n    12→\n    13→    @Id\n    14→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)\n    15→    public Long id;\n    16→\n    17→    @Column(name = \"first_name\")\n    18→    @NotEmpty\n    19→    public String firstName;\n    20→\n    21→    @Column(name = \"last_name\")\n    22→    @NotEmpty\n    23→    public String lastName;\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    public String toString() {\n    27→        return \"Person [firstName=\" + firstName + \", lastName=\" + lastName + \"]\";\n    28→    }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"12ee9f19-9c53-41e9-a262-6fa2afdf27a0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DXjoeGpeqhFQZAqTrD53h8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `showOwner` method at line 74 calls `em.find(Owner.class, ownerId)` but doesn't call `setVisits()` like `processFindForm` does. That's not the main issue though - the problem is that the owner with ID 1001 IS in the import.sql. The issue from the smoke test output was that the body contained just the base layout HTML without the owner details content - suggesting the `em.find` returned null. \n\nThis is likely because with H2's IDENTITY strategy and Hibernate's `create-drop`, when Hibernate creates the table, it might use `GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY`. The explicit IDs in import.sql (1001) should work with `GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY`, but the column ordering in the INSERT might be wrong.\n\nLet me look at how the INSERT is structured: `INSERT INTO owners VALUES (1001, 'George', 'Franklin', '110 W. Liberty St.', 'Madison', '6085551023')`. The owners table has columns: id, first_name, last_name, address, city, telephone. This should match. The issue might be something else. Let me rebuild, start the container, and check the actual error:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4544,"cache_read_input_tokens":102567,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4544,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":394},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"1e7cc246-6cc2-4ad4-8db9-83b1b1d8e99e"}
