{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013zg4b77NESWMcrXBNPVRkZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.HashMap;\n     4→import java.util.Map;\n     5→\n     6→/**\n     7→ * Application message constants.\n     8→ * Replaces Quarkus Qute @MessageBundle with a simple Map.\n     9→ */\n    10→public class AppMessages {\n    11→\n    12→    private static final Map<String, String> MESSAGES = new HashMap<>();\n    13→\n    14→    static {\n    15→        MESSAGES.put(\"find_owner\", \"Find Owner\");\n    16→        MESSAGES.put(\"last_name\", \"Last Name\");\n    17→        MESSAGES.put(\"edit_owner\", \"Edit Owner\");\n    18→        MESSAGES.put(\"add_owner\", \"Add Owner\");\n    19→        MESSAGES.put(\"find_owners\", \"Find Owners\");\n    20→        MESSAGES.put(\"name\", \"Name\");\n    21→        MESSAGES.put(\"address\", \"Address\");\n    22→        MESSAGES.put(\"telephone\", \"Telephone\");\n    23→        MESSAGES.put(\"city\", \"City\");\n    24→        MESSAGES.put(\"pets\", \"Pets\");\n    25→        MESSAGES.put(\"pet\", \"Pet\");\n    26→        MESSAGES.put(\"error\", \"Error\");\n    27→        MESSAGES.put(\"none\", \"None\");\n    28→        MESSAGES.put(\"veterinarians\", \"Veterinarians\");\n    29→        MESSAGES.put(\"specialties\", \"Specialties\");\n    30→        MESSAGES.put(\"welcome\", \"Welcome\");\n    31→        MESSAGES.put(\"birthdate\", \"Birthdate\");\n    32→        MESSAGES.put(\"type\", \"Type\");\n    33→        MESSAGES.put(\"owner\", \"Owner\");\n    34→        MESSAGES.put(\"edit_pet\", \"Edit Pet\");\n    35→        MESSAGES.put(\"add_pet\", \"Add Pet\");\n    36→        MESSAGES.put(\"add_visit\", \"Add Visit\");\n    37→        MESSAGES.put(\"visit_date\", \"Visit Date\");\n    38→        MESSAGES.put(\"description\", \"Description\");\n    39→        MESSAGES.put(\"new_\", \"New\");\n    40→        MESSAGES.put(\"visit\", \"Visit\");\n    41→        MESSAGES.put(\"date\", \"Date\");\n    42→        MESSAGES.put(\"home\", \"Home\");\n    43→        MESSAGES.put(\"pets_and_visits\", \"Pets and Visits\");\n    44→        MESSAGES.put(\"previous_visits\", \"Previous Visits\");\n    45→        MESSAGES.put(\"something_wrong\", \"Something happened...\");\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public static Map<String, String> getMessages() {\n    49→        return MESSAGES;\n    50→    }\n    51→}\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7877d114-a8cd-4b86-860b-21ca41dfcbd5","uuid":"001d6dc1-bc28-4e0c-ac03-212885fcd580"}
